ng",[17,177,178],{},"For the next screen I picked the first option:",[109,180,181,184],{},[112,182,183],{},"Standalone MySQL Server \u002F Classic MySQL Replication",[112,185,186],{},"InnoDB Cluster",[17,188,189],{},[38,190],{"alt":191,"src":192},"Standalone MySQL Server","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FMywhRil.png",[17,194,195],{},"The next screen is MySQL config (port etc.). Default values are fine — Next.",[17,197,198],{},[38,199],{"alt":200,"src":201},"MySQL config","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F9B7KfNA.png",[17,203,204],{},"Authentication method — first option:",[109,206,207,210],{},[112,208,209],{},"Use Strong Password Encryption for Authentication (RECOMMENDED)",[112,211,212],{},"Use Legacy Authentication Method (Retain MySQL 5.x Compatibility)",[17,214,215,216,220],{},"Heads up: if you pick ",[217,218,219],"strong",{},"Strong Password Encryption"," and use Navicat like me, you'll hit a connection issue. I added the fix at the bottom of this post.",[17,222,223,224,227],{},"I'd actually recommend picking ",[217,225,226],{},"Legacy Authentication Method"," to dodge a lot of problems and keep Navicat working.",[17,229,230],{},[38,231],{"alt":232,"src":233},"Authentication method","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F0f9GmTl.png",[17,235,236,237,240],{},"Security — set the root password. This is super important, don't leak it. ",[73,238,239],{},"root"," is MySQL's superuser.",[17,242,243],{},[38,244],{"alt":239,"src":245},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FSaeIHig.png",[17,247,248],{},"Add a user account.",[17,250,251],{},[38,252],{"alt":253,"src":254},"Add user","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FbsyPGWz.png",[17,256,257],{},"Configure as needed:",[109,259,260,263,270],{},[112,261,262],{},"UserName — account name",[112,264,265,266,269],{},"Host — allowed login domain. ",[73,267,268],{},"%"," allows any",[112,271,272],{},"Role — permissions",[17,274,275],{},[38,276],{"alt":253,"src":277},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002Ffe3PyTI.png",[17,279,280],{},[38,281],{"alt":253,"src":282},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FWly4TwL.png",[17,284,285],{},"Next is Windows service setup. Default's fine — Next.",[17,287,288],{},[38,289],{"alt":290,"src":291},"Windows service","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FfLatDCO.png",[17,293,294],{},"There's one option you might want to tweak — whether MySQL auto-starts with Windows.",[17,296,297],{},[38,298],{"alt":299,"src":300},"MySQL auto-start","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FiifCa11.png",[17,302,303],{},"Review your settings and click Execute.",[17,305,306],{},[38,307],{"alt":158,"src":308},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FxpRoasN.png",[17,310,311],{},"After the config runs, Finish.",[17,313,314],{},[38,315],{"alt":316,"src":317},"Finish","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FZWflTzP.png",[17,319,320],{},"This screen asks if you want to configure more products. Cancel.",[17,322,323],{},[38,324],{"alt":325,"src":326},"Cancel","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FpHq5fz8.png",[17,328,329],{},"Click Yes.",[17,331,332],{},[38,333],{"alt":149,"src":334},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FeLSA6Mu.png",[12,336,338],{"id":337},"how-to-confirm-mysql-is-running","How to confirm MySQL is running",[17,340,341],{},"Open Task Manager, switch to Services, look for MySQL 8.",[17,343,344],{},[38,345],{"alt":346,"src":347},"Image","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FHT6uJHh.png",[12,349,351],{"id":350},"connecting-to-mysql","Connecting to MySQL",[17,353,354,355,358],{},"Use ",[73,356,357],{},"MySQL 8.0 Command Line Client"," — double-click it, enter your password.",[17,360,361],{},[38,362],{"alt":357,"src":363},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FhFyFIv7.png",[365,366,368],"h3",{"id":367},"current-user","Current user",[17,370,371],{},"To check the logged-in user:",[373,374,378],"pre",{"className":375,"code":376,"language":22,"meta":377,"style":377},"language-mysql shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","select user();\n","",[73,379,380],{"__ignoreMap":377},[381,382,385],"span",{"class":383,"line":384},"line",1,[381,386,376],{},[17,388,389],{},"OR",[373,391,393],{"className":375,"code":392,"language":22,"meta":377,"style":377},"SELECT CURRENT_USER();\n",[73,394,395],{"__ignoreMap":377},[381,396,397],{"class":383,"line":384},[381,398,392],{},[17,400,401],{},[38,402],{"alt":368,"src":403},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FpbYjtuo.png",[365,405,407],{"id":406},"check-mysql-version","Check MySQL version",[373,409,411],{"className":375,"code":410,"language":22,"meta":377,"style":377},"mysql -V\n",[73,412,413],{"__ignoreMap":377},[381,414,415],{"class":383,"line":384},[381,416,410],{},[12,418,420],{"id":419},"navicat-connection-fix","Navicat connection fix",[17,422,423],{},"I usually use Navicat for MySQL.",[17,425,426,427,430],{},"When connecting, I got ",[73,428,429],{},"client does not support authentication protocol requested by server",".",[17,432,433],{},"This is because of MySQL 8's new authentication. Either use a newer Navicat or switch MySQL 8's auth back. See:",[17,435,436],{},[28,437,440],{"href":438,"rel":439},"https:\u002F\u002Fblog.csdn.net\u002Fweixin_33862993\u002Farticle\u002Fdetails\u002F88152318",[32],"Navicat for MySQL — error 1251 (in Chinese)",[442,443,444],"style",{},"html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}html .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: var(--shiki-default-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-default-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-default-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-default-text-decoration);}",{"title":377,"searchDepth":446,"depth":446,"links":447},2,[448,449,450,451,452,457],{"id":14,"depth":446,"text":15},{"id":22,"depth":446,"text":23},{"id":85,"depth":446,"text":86},{"id":337,"depth":446,"text":338},{"id":350,"depth":446,"text":351,"children":453},[454,456],{"id":367,"depth":455,"text":368},3